Thanks for filing the issue @mahdeto. Note that we primarily use github issues to track bugs and feature requests. This is a question better suited for StackOverflow. Please ask it there and tag it with the tensorflow tag. Thanks!

As for the error you're encountering, I'd suggest starting with the provided example code:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/examples/learn/wide_n_deep_tutorial.py

If you can boil the problem down to that example code, or a small change to that example code, feel free to comment on this issue or file a new issue.
